From 422fe04a7ceb46573b9f69ef5fdb181ba00eebac Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: lucascouts <lucascs@protonmail.com>
Date: Wed, 8 Jul 2026 19:01:24 -0300
Subject: [PATCH 7/8] feat(agent_ui): manual-mode badge next to the mode
 selector

Cover both mode-surface paths. Agents that expose session modes get the
badge in ModeSelector; agents that return session configOptions (the
claude-agent-acp-plus adapter) never instantiate ModeSelector -- Zed
renders ConfigOptionSelector instead -- so the badge is now also
rendered next to the Mode-category select trigger while its current
value id is `default` (R4.1) and cleared on any other mode (R4.2). The
badge element is identical on both paths (R4.3); the id predicate is
shared via mode_selector::shows_manual_mode_badge.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
